<Link id="l00077" /><CodeLine lineNumber="77"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00078" /><CodeLine lineNumber="78"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Walk the block backwards, move PSEUDO&#95;PROBE before the first real</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00079" /><CodeLine lineNumber="79"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instruction to fix out-of-order probes. There is a problem with probes</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00080" /><CodeLine lineNumber="80"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// as the terminator of the block. During the offline counts processing,</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00081" /><CodeLine lineNumber="81"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the samples collected on the first physical instruction following a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00082" /><CodeLine lineNumber="82"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// probe will be counted towards the probe. This logically equals to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00083" /><CodeLine lineNumber="83"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// treating the instruction next to a probe as if it is from the same</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00084" /><CodeLine lineNumber="84"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// block of the probe. This is accurate most of the time unless the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00085" /><CodeLine lineNumber="85"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// instruction can be reached from multiple flows, which means it actually</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00086" /><CodeLine lineNumber="86"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// starts a new block. Samples collected on such probes may cause</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00087" /><CodeLine lineNumber="87"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// imprecision with the counts inference algorithm. Fortunately, if</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00088" /><CodeLine lineNumber="88"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// there are still other native instructions preceding the probe we can</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00089" /><CodeLine lineNumber="89"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// use them as a place holder to collect samples for the probe.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00090" /><CodeLine lineNumber="90"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (FirstInstr) &#123;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00092" /><CodeLine lineNumber="92"><span class="doxyHighlight">        </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">while</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (MII != <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/arm/armslshardening-cpp/#a5958512eae2979bd2eb383977996a600">MBB</a>.rend()) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00093" /><CodeLine lineNumber="93"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Skip all pseudo probes followed by a real instruction since they</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00094" /><CodeLine lineNumber="94"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// are not dangling.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00095" /><CodeLine lineNumber="95"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!MII-&gt;isPseudo())</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00096" /><CodeLine lineNumber="96"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">break</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00098" /><CodeLine lineNumber="98"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Cur-&gt;getOpcode() != TargetOpcode::PSEUDO&#95;PROBE)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00099" /><CodeLine lineNumber="99"><span class="doxyHighlight">            </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">continue</span><span class="doxyHighlight">;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00100" /><CodeLine lineNumber="100"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Move the dangling probe before FirstInstr.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00101" /><CodeLine lineNumber="101"><span class="doxyHighlight">          </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">auto</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> &#42;ProbeInstr = &amp;&#42;Cur;</span></CodeLine>
